It&#8217;s understood the man killed was Raymond 'Razor' Barras, who was well-known in underworld circles in eastern Johannesburg. JOHANNESBURG - Police have confirmed that a man was shot and killed in Kensington in eastern Johannesburg on Wednesday morning.The man is known to have links to the criminal underworld, but police and sources say it is unclear at this stage if the shooting was a hijacking or a hit.It s understood that the man killed was Raymond 'Razor' Barras, who was well-known in underworld circles in eastern Johannesburg.He was shot outside his house in Highland Road in Kensington.Underworld sources say Barras had recently been moving in the illegal cigarette trade and spent some time doing business in Cape Town.(Edited by Shimoney Regter)